### ============================================
### P24 PAYMENT FLOW TEST - HAPPY PATH
### ============================================

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000

### Step 1: Register Light (creates user + cookie)
# @name registerLight
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register-light
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "patient-p24-test@example.com",
  "firstName": "Test",
  "lastName": "Patient"
}

### Step 2: Create Doc with Profile and Slot (MANUALLY IN DB OR SEED)
# You need:
# - A doc user with docProfile (sessionPricePln set, published=true)
# - An availability slot (booked=false, startTime in future)
# Use seed script or prisma studio

### Step 3: Create Meeting (replace docId and slotId with real values)
# @name createMeeting
POST {{baseUrl}}/meetings
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "docId": 1,
  "slotId": 1,
  "clientMessage": "Looking forward to P24 payment test"
}

### Step 4: Start P24 Payment (use meetingId from step 3)
# @name startP24
POST {{baseUrl}}/payments/p24/start
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "meetingId": 1
}

### Expected response:
# {
#   "url": "https://sandbox.przelewy24.pl/trnRequest/TOKEN",
#   "token": "TOKEN_FROM_P24",
#   "sessionId": "melius-meeting-1-pay-1"
# }

### Step 5: Simulate P24 Webhook (use sessionId from step 4)
POST {{baseUrl}}/payments/p24/webhook
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sessionId": "melius-meeting-1-pay-1",
  "orderId": 999999,
  "amount": 22000
}

### Expected behavior:
# - Backend calls P24 /transaction/verify
# - If verify succeeds: Payment status -> succeeded, Meeting status -> confirmed
# - If verify fails: Payment status -> failed
# - Check logs for verification result

### Step 6: Verify Meeting Status
GET {{baseUrl}}/meetings/me

### Expected: Meeting should have status "confirmed" if P24 verify succeeded
